<h3>Architecture</h3>
<p>Navigation is a <strong>Module</strong> composed of two behaviors and enhanced router integration:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>NavListBehavior</strong> (<code>nav:list</code>): Attaches to a <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> element. Manages roving tabindex across all navigation links, tracks <code>aria-current="page"</code> for active state, and handles arrow key navigation.</li>
  <li><strong>NavSectionBehavior</strong> (<code>nav:section</code>): Attaches to a collapsible section container. Implements the disclosure pattern with a toggle button that controls <code>aria-expanded</code> and shows/hides the section's link list.</li>
  <li><strong>RouteLinkBehavior</strong> (from Router): Enhanced with <code>aria-current="page"</code> support. When a route matches, the corresponding link receives both the <code>.active</code> CSS class and the <code>aria-current="page"</code> attribute.</li>
</ul>
<p>NavListBehavior observes the DOM for <code>aria-current</code> changes (via MutationObserver or router events) and updates the roving tabindex accordingly &mdash; the currently active page link receives <code>tabindex="0"</code>.</p>

<h3>HTML Usage</h3>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;nav nav:list aria-label="Main navigation"&gt;
  &lt;!-- Top-level links --&gt;
  &lt;a href="/" route:link&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;a href="/about" route:link&gt;About&lt;/a&gt;

  &lt;!-- Collapsible section --&gt;
  &lt;div nav:section&gt;
    &lt;button aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="docs-links"&gt;
      Documentation
    &lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;ul id="docs-links"&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/docs/getting-started" route:link&gt;Getting Started&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/docs/api" route:link&gt;API Reference&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/docs/examples" route:link&gt;Examples&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- Another collapsible section (initially collapsed) --&gt;
  &lt;div nav:section&gt;
    &lt;button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="guides-links"&gt;
      Guides
    &lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;ul id="guides-links" hidden&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/guides/routing" route:link&gt;Routing&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/guides/state" route:link&gt;State Management&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/nav&gt;</code></pre>

<h3>ARIA Implementation</h3>
<p>Follows the <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/disclosure/examples/disclosure-navigation/">W3C APG Disclosure Navigation</a> pattern:</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Element</th><th>Managed By</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td><code>aria-label</code></td><td><code>&lt;nav&gt;</code></td><td>Author</td><td>Identifies the navigation landmark when multiple exist on the page</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>aria-current="page"</code></td><td><code>&lt;a&gt;</code></td><td>RouteLinkBehavior</td><td>Identifies the link matching the current URL; announced by screen readers as "current page"</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>aria-expanded</code></td><td><code>&lt;button&gt;</code></td><td>NavSectionBehavior</td><td>Communicates whether the section is expanded or collapsed</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>aria-controls</code></td><td><code>&lt;button&gt;</code></td><td>NavSectionBehavior</td><td>Associates the toggle button with the controlled section content</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>tabindex="0"</code></td><td>Active link</td><td>NavListBehavior</td><td>Makes the currently focused/active navigation item tabbable</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>tabindex="-1"</code></td><td>Other links</td><td>NavListBehavior</td><td>Removes other links from tab order; reachable only via arrow keys</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Keyboard Interaction</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Key</th><th>Context</th><th>Action</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Arrow Down</td><td>Navigation list</td><td>Move focus to next link</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Arrow Up</td><td>Navigation list</td><td>Move focus to previous link</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Home</td><td>Navigation list</td><td>Move focus to first link</td></tr>
  <tr><td>End</td><td>Navigation list</td><td>Move focus to last link</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Enter</td><td>Link</td><td>Navigate to the link target</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Enter / Space</td><td>Section toggle button</td><td>Toggle the section expanded/collapsed state</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Escape</td><td>Expanded section</td><td>Collapse the section and return focus to the toggle button</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Configuration</h3>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;!-- Orientation: vertical (default) or horizontal --&gt;
&lt;nav nav:list orientation="vertical"&gt;...&lt;/nav&gt;
&lt;nav nav:list orientation="horizontal"&gt;...&lt;/nav&gt;

&lt;!-- Auto-expand section containing the current page link --&gt;
&lt;div nav:section auto-expand&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Collapse other sections when one is expanded (accordion mode) --&gt;
&lt;nav nav:list exclusive-sections&gt;...&lt;/nav&gt;</code></pre>

<h3>Router Integration</h3>
<p>When used with the <a href="/blocks/router/">Router</a>, navigation links use <code>route:link</code> to get automatic active state management:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>route:link</code> intercepts clicks for SPA navigation</li>
  <li>On route change, the matching link receives <code>aria-current="page"</code> and <code>.active</code> class</li>
  <li>NavListBehavior observes these changes and updates roving tabindex to match</li>
  <li>Sections containing the active link can auto-expand via the <code>auto-expand</code> attribute</li>
</ul>

<h3>Styling Hooks</h3>
<pre><code class="language-css">/* Active link (current page) */
[nav\:list] a[aria-current="page"] {
  font-weight: bold;
  border-left: 3px solid var(--color-primary);
}

/* Focused link (keyboard navigation) */
[nav\:list] a:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-focus);
  outline-offset: -2px;
}

/* Expanded section toggle */
[nav\:section] button[aria-expanded="true"] {
  color: var(--color-primary);
}

/* Collapsed section content */
[nav\:section] [hidden] {
  display: none;
}

/* Respect reduced motion */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  [nav\:section] ul {
    transition: none;
  }
}</code></pre>

<h3>Exports</h3>
<ul>
  <li><code>NavListBehavior</code> &mdash; Keyboard navigation and active state tracking behavior (<code>nav:list</code>)</li>
  <li><code>NavSectionBehavior</code> &mdash; Disclosure toggle behavior for collapsible sections (<code>nav:section</code>)</li>
  <li><code>registerNavigation</code> &mdash; Registers both behaviors with the attribute registry</li>
</ul>
